# Purpose
That is demonstration on demand validation used in PyPSA-Earth to model Kazakhstan power system

# Data sources
Outputs of GEGIS for demand predictions are compared against data provided by Kazakhstan Electricity and Power Market Operator (KEGOS).

# How to run
1. Install R (either as base R https://cran.r-project.org/bin/ or as R Studio https://posit.co/products/open-source/rstudio/)
2. Run R console in the folder of project. The working folder can be adjusted by `setwd(project_dir)` directly in R session.
3. In R console 
    * run `install.packages("tidyverse", "lubridate")` to install R extentions used in further calculations
    * run a source file with `source("demand_valid.R")`